      <title>Catch That Bus/Train</title>
      <link>https://fergul.github.io/project/trainkindledisplay/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 27 Apr 2016 00:00:00 +0100</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://fergul.github.io/project/trainkindledisplay/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Ever wanted to know if you needed to run to catch that bus or train&amp;hellip;no, well I did!&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A simple ambient display to show bus and train times for a local stop, with weather info to let you know if you need an jacket on the way out.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Uses a kindle display to non-intrusively show info and looks great on its non-backlit e-paper display.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Written in Python utilising the MetOffice and TfL open data APIs to grab weather and transport information, respectively.&lt;/p&gt;



